3ï¸âƒ£ Where is the webhook configured?
On GitHub / GitLab side

You configure:

URL: https://jenkins.example.com/github-webhook/

Event: push / pull_request

Secret (HMAC)

GitHub sends JSON payload like:

{
  "ref": "refs/heads/main",
  "after": "commit_hash",
  "repository": {...}
}

4ï¸âƒ£ What does Jenkins do with that webhook?

In Jenkins:

Job is configured as â€œGitHub webhook triggerâ€

Jenkins verifies signature

Jenkins pulls code

Jenkins runs pipeline

Example Jenkinsfile:

pipeline {
  stages {
    stage('Test') {
      steps { sh 'bundle exec rspec' }
    }
    stage('Build Docker') {
      steps { sh 'docker build -t app .' }
    }
    stage('Deploy') {
      steps { sh 'ecs deploy ...' }
    }
  }
}

